# HTTP security response headers for the published SPA.
#
# How this ships: Vite copies everything in `public/` verbatim into `dist/`, so
# this file is served as `dist/_headers`. The host applies it to every response
# — Cloudflare Workers static assets (see wrangler.toml), Cloudflare Pages,
# Netlify, and the Lovable publish pipeline all read a top-level `_headers`
# file. No wrangler.toml change is required.
#
# Format notes (important): `_headers` does NOT support line continuations, so
# every header value must stay on a single physical line. The path pattern
# (`/*`) is unindented; the header lines below it are indented.
#
# Rollout: the first block of headers is safe to enforce immediately. The
# Content-Security-Policy is shipped in *Report-Only* mode so it can never break
# the live site — the browser only logs would-be violations to the console.
# Once the console is clean in production, rename the header from
# `Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only` to `Content-Security-Policy` to enforce.
#
# `tests/securityHeaders.test.ts` is a smoke test that guards these values.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  X-XSS-Protection: 0
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), autoplay=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), encrypted-media=(), fullscreen=(self), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), midi=(), payment=(), picture-in-picture=(), usb=(), xr-spatial-tracking=()
